Hong Kong museums are proud to feature a variety of new exhibits.  

The Hong Kong Museum of Art is showing pieces of Italian Baroque Art, twentieth century "Cobra" movement works, and modern French art.

Also, the Science Museum is exhibiting Chinese Dinosaur fossils.  The Museum of History has an exhibit on modern Chinese history.
 Several museums in Hong Kong, the Hong Kong Museum of Art, the Hong Kong Museum of History, and the Hong Kong Science Museum are displaying a wide variety of exhibits, including "The Rise of China," dinosaur fossils from china and around the globe, and European artists from different periods.
 Many art, science, and history exhibitions are on display in Hong Kong. The Museum of Art will present many exhibitions, from Chinese art to French art.
The Museum of History has a "Rise of Modern China" exhibition on display.
